sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION — Added risk assessment decision with expedited path for low-risk customers
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Credit Score, Company Status, Payment History)
    alt Low-Risk (Score >750 AND Verified Company AND Clean Payment History)
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved – Low Risk (Expedited)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited path)
    else High-Risk
        F->>F: Escalate to Finance Director
        F-->>S: Finance Director Approval (24h SLA)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
    end
    %% END CHANGED SECTION
    IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the single Finance approval step with a risk assessment performed by Finance. An `alt` block now branches the flow: low-risk customers (credit score >750, verified company status, clean payment history) receive automatic approval and proceed directly to expedited account provisioning, while high-risk customers are escalated to the Finance Director for the existing 24h SLA approval before provisioning. All downstream steps (welcome email, first login, onboarding complete, kickoff meeting) remain unchanged for both paths.